text: this might only be a cool idea in my head, but i was looking at laundry studio’s website and was thinking about all of the cool code art that gaston works on, and wouldnt it be b adass to do some sort of uncorked x laundry collaboration? i have no idea what that would be, but they’re our neighbors and their work is really cool.

text: I’d love that. I’ve been to a few events of that sort. That format that seems to work best is some sort of dedicated time. Say, an afternoon where we collaborate and have to have something by the end of the day.
If you make something long it drags and then projects get in the way nothing ever gets done. IMO.
They seem to do stuff with fabric/apparel. Something like this would be awesome: <https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/fbz/knityak-custom-mathematical-knit-scarves>
